  "text": "[…] Today, just as back then, very extensive areas of extreme poverty can be found even in the rich countries. There are outrageous, widening inequalities between countries, as well as between social classes\" (Badiou, 2010, pp. 258f) . \"More than ever, political power, as the current economic crisis with its one single slogan of 'rescue the banks' clearly proves, is merely an agent of capitalism\" (Badiou, 2010, p. 259) . Badiou says that the call \"save the banks\" shows that there is not an \"end of ideologies\" (Badiou, 2010, p. 99) and that therefore today nothing \"could be more important than rediscovering the passion for ideas\" (Badiou, 2010, p. 100) . Therefore a general hypothesis that \"we can create a very different order of things\" [CITATION_1] , 100) would be needed. Therefore a counter-idea would be needed. Badiou says that \"we have to be bold enough to have an idea\" (Badiou, 2010, p. 66) . This counterhypothesis would mean \"to cling to the historical hypothesis of a world that has been freed from the law of profit and private interest\" (Badiou, 2010, p. 63) , a world that is an association, \"in which the free development of each is the condition for the free development of all\" (Badiou, 2010, p. 100 ).",
